<content type="application/x.deki0805+xml" title="spacer"><body xmlns:eval="http://mindtouch.com/2007/dekiscript"><div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div> <p>An element that takes up space but does not display anything. It is usually used to place spacing within a container. If you don't specify that the spacer has a size or is flexible, the spacer does not occupy any space. If you want a small gap, consider using a <span class="script">template.XULElem("separator")</span> instead.
</p><p>More information is available in the <a href="en/XUL_Tutorial/Using_Spacers">XUL tutorial</a>.
</p>
<h3 name="Examples"> Examples </h3>
<pre class="eval">&lt;box&gt;
  &lt;button label="Left"/&gt;
  &lt;spacer flex="1"/&gt;
  &lt;button label="Right"/&gt;
&lt;/box&gt;
</pre>
